(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Precursor"는 선구자, 전조라는 뜻입니다.', '["precursor", "successor", "descendant", "heir"]', 'The heavy, dark clouds rolling over the mountains were a clear ______ to a massive storm.', 'en_ad_145', 145, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Confluence"는 합일, 융합이라는 뜻입니다.', '["divergence", "confluence", "bifurcation", "separation"]', 'The city is located at the ______ of three major rivers, making it a natural hub for trade.', 'en_ad_146', 146, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Impediment"는 장애(물)라는 뜻입니다.', '["catalyst", "stimulus", "impediment", "boon"]', 'His severe stutter was a major ______ to his career as a public speaker.', 'en_ad_147', 147, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Affinity"는 친밀감, 관련성이라는 뜻입니다.', '["aversion", "disgust", "antipathy", "affinity"]', 'Having grown up by the ocean, the sailor felt a natural ______ for the sea.', 'en_ad_148', 148, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Antipathy"는 반감, 혐오라는 뜻입니다.', '["antipathy", "fondness", "predilection", "penchant"]', 'The two rival teams shared a mutual ______ that often resulted in brawls on the field.', 'en_ad_149', 149, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Resurgence"는 부활, 재기라는 뜻입니다.', '["decline", "resurgence", "extinction", "waning"]', 'Vinyl records have experienced a massive ______ in popularity among younger generations recently.', 'en_ad_150', 150, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Demise"는 종말, 죽음이라는 뜻입니다.', '["genesis", "inception", "demise", "birth"]', 'The invention of the automobile eventually led to the ______ of the horse-drawn carriage industry.', 'en_ad_151', 151, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Anachronism"은 시대착오적인 사람/사물이라는 뜻입니다.', '["innovation", "novelty", "vanguard", "anachronism"]', 'Seeing a knight in full armor using a smartphone in the movie was a glaring ______.', 'en_ad_152', 152, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Oxymoron"은 모순어법(예: deafening silence)이라는 뜻입니다.', '["oxymoron", "hyperbole", "simile", "metaphor"]', 'The phrase "jumbo shrimp" is a classic example of an ______.', 'en_ad_153', 153, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Tautology"는 유의어 반복(불필요한 중복)이라는 뜻입니다.', '["conciseness", "tautology", "brevity", "economy"]', 'Saying "the widow of the late president" is a ______ because a widow''s husband is by definition dead.', 'en_ad_154', 154, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Hyperbole"는 과장법이라는 뜻입니다.', '["understatement", "litotes", "hyperbole", "euphemism"]', 'Claiming you are so hungry you could eat a horse is a common form of ______.', 'en_ad_155', 155, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Demagogue"는 선동 정치가라는 뜻입니다.', '["statesman", "diplomat", "peacemaker", "demagogue"]', 'The dictator rose to power not through rational debate, but by acting as a ______ who exploited the crowd''s fears.', 'en_ad_156', 156, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Philanthropist"는 자선가라는 뜻입니다.', '["philanthropist", "miser", "skinflint", "extortionist"]', 'The billionaire ______ donated 90% of his fortune to build schools in developing nations.', 'en_ad_157', 157, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Polyglot"은 여러 언어를 아는(사람)이라는 뜻입니다.', '["monolingual", "polyglot", "illiterate", "novice"]', 'As a true ______, she could seamlessly switch between speaking English, Mandarin, Arabic, and French.', 'en_ad_158', 158, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Martinet"은 엄격한 규율가라는 뜻입니다.', '["libertine", "anarchist", "martinet", "bohemian"]', 'The new drill sergeant was a ______ who punished recruits for having even a speck of dust on their boots.', 'en_ad_159', 159, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Dilettante"는 아마추어 (예술) 애호가, 호사가라는 뜻입니다.', '["expert", "professional", "maestro", "dilettante"]', 'He dabbled in painting, writing, and music, but remained a ______ without mastering any single craft.', 'en_ad_160', 160, 12),

-- 161~180: Advanced Word Definitions (영영 사전식 단어 정의)
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Tyro"는 초보자라는 뜻입니다.', '["tyro", "veteran", "doyen", "virtuoso"]', 'Which word refers to a beginner or novice in learning a certain skill or profession?', 'en_ad_161', 161, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Virtuoso"는 거장, 명연주자라는 뜻입니다.', '["amateur", "virtuoso", "dabbler", "apprentice"]', 'What is the term for a person highly skilled in music or another artistic pursuit?', 'en_ad_162', 162, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Charlatan"은 사기꾼, 돌팔이라는 뜻입니다.', '["savant", "expert", "charlatan", "luminary"]', 'Which word describes a person falsely claiming to have a special knowledge or skill?', 'en_ad_163', 163, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Maverick"은 개성이 강한 독립적인 사람, 이단아라는 뜻입니다.', '["conformist", "follower", "traditionalist", "maverick"]', 'What term is used for an unorthodox or independent-minded person?', 'en_ad_164', 164, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Chauvinist"는 맹목적 애국주의자, 차별주의자라는 뜻입니다.', '["chauvinist", "egalitarian", "pacifist", "humanitarian"]', 'Which word refers to a person displaying aggressive or exaggerated patriotism or prejudice?', 'en_ad_165', 165, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Hedonist"는 쾌락주의자라는 뜻입니다.', '["ascetic", "hedonist", "puritan", "stoic"]', 'What is the term for a person who believes that the pursuit of pleasure is the most important thing in life?', 'en_ad_166', 166, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Ascetic"은 금욕주의자라는 뜻입니다.', '["epicurean", "sybarite", "ascetic", "glutton"]', 'Which word describes a person who practices severe self-discipline and abstention from all forms of indulgence?', 'en_ad_167', 167, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Cynic"은 냉소주의자라는 뜻입니다.', '["optimist", "idealist", "believer", "cynic"]', 'What term refers to a person who believes that people are motivated purely by self-interest?', 'en_ad_168', 168, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Fatalist"는 운명론자라는 뜻입니다.', '["fatalist", "activist", "visionary", "utopian"]', 'Which word describes someone who feels that no matter what he or she does, the outcome will be the same because it is predetermined?', 'en_ad_169', 169, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Meticulous"는 꼼꼼한 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["careless", "meticulous", "slapdash", "cursory"]', 'What adjective means showing great attention to detail; very careful and precise?', 'en_ad_170', 170, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Obfuscate"는 애매하게 하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["clarify", "illuminate", "obfuscate", "simplify"]', 'Which verb means to render obscure, unclear, or unintelligible?', 'en_ad_171', 171, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Alleviate"는 완화하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["aggravate", "exacerbate", "heighten", "alleviate"]', 'What word signifies making suffering, deficiency, or a problem less severe?', 'en_ad_172', 172, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Pernicious"는 해로운 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["pernicious", "beneficial", "advantageous", "salubrious"]', 'Which adjective describes a highly injurious or destructive effect, especially in a gradual manner?', 'en_ad_173', 173, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Ephemeral"은 일시적인 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["lasting", "ephemeral", "permanent", "endless"]', 'What term means lasting for a very short duration?', 'en_ad_174', 174, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Equivocal"은 모호한 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["certain", "definite", "equivocal", "indisputable"]', 'Which word describes language open to more than one interpretation; ambiguous?', 'en_ad_175', 175, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Garrulous"는 수다스러운 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["concise", "terse", "mute", "garrulous"]', 'What adjective means excessively talkative, especially on trivial matters?', 'en_ad_176', 176, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Intransigent"는 고집스러운 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["intransigent", "flexible", "compromising", "yielding"]', 'Which word refers to being unwilling or refusing to change one''s views or to agree about something?', 'en_ad_177', 177, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Platitude"는 진부한 말이라는 뜻입니다.', '["innovation", "platitude", "revelation", "originality"]', 'What is the term for a remark or statement, especially one with a moral content, that has been used too often to be interesting?', 'en_ad_178', 178, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Synergistic"은 상승효과가 있는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["antagonistic", "opposing", "synergistic", "conflicting"]', 'Which adjective describes different elements working together to produce an effect greater than the sum of their individual effects?', 'en_ad_179', 179, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Cacophony"는 불협화음이라는 뜻입니다.', '["melody", "symphony", "harmony", "cacophony"]', 'What word refers to a harsh, discordant mixture of sounds?', 'en_ad_180', 180, 12),

-- 181~200: High-Level Grammar & Phrasal Idioms (최상급 영문법 및 관용구)
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '부정어구 Scarcely 도치입니다. Scarcely had S p.p ~ when S 과거동사 구문입니다.', '["had I closed", "I had closed", "did I close", "I closed"]', 'Scarcely ______ my eyes when the terrifying earthquake struck the city.', 'en_ad_181', 181, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'lest S (should) V (~하지 않기 위해서) 구문입니다.', '["will", "should", "would", "might"]', 'He locked the highly classified documents in the safe lest anyone ______ steal them.', 'en_ad_182', 182, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Provided that은 만약 ~라면(If)의 뜻을 가진 고급 접속사입니다.', '["Due to", "In case", "Provided that", "Unless"]', '______ you sign the non-disclosure agreement, we will share the prototype with you.', 'en_ad_183', 183, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Granted that은 비록 ~일지라도(Even if, admitting that)의 뜻입니다.', '["Seeing that", "Now that", "Except that", "Granted that"]', '______ he is a genius, his arrogance makes him impossible to work with.', 'en_ad_184', 184, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Inasmuch as는 ~인 점을 고려하면, ~이므로(Since)의 뜻입니다.', '["Inasmuch as", "As long as", "So far as", "As well as"]', '______ the budget is severely limited, we must cancel the annual retreat.', 'en_ad_185', 185, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Notwithstanding은 ~에도 불구하고(Despite)의 뜻을 가진 전치사/부사입니다.', '["Instead of", "Notwithstanding", "According to", "Prior to"]', '______ the heavy criticism from the press, the mayor pushed forward with his tax reform.', 'en_ad_186', 186, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'For all은 ~에도 불구하고(Despite)의 뜻을 가진 관용구입니다.', '["In favor of", "On behalf of", "For all", "Thanks to"]', '______ his immense wealth and power, he lived a remarkably isolated and lonely life.', 'en_ad_187', 187, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'By virtue of는 ~덕분에, ~의 힘으로라는 뜻입니다.', '["In violation of", "In search of", "At the risk of", "By virtue of"]', 'She was appointed as the head of the department ______ her unparalleled expertise in genetics.', 'en_ad_188', 188, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'In lieu of는 ~대신에(Instead of)라는 뜻의 관용구입니다.', '["In lieu of", "In light of", "In charge of", "In terms of"]', 'The company offered employees extra vacation days ______ a cash bonus this year.', 'en_ad_189', 189, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'At the mercy of는 ~에 휘둘리는, ~의 처분대로 되는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["At the expense of", "At the mercy of", "On the brink of", "For the sake of"]', 'Without an engine, the small sailboat was completely ______ the raging storm.', 'en_ad_190', 190, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'A far cry from은 ~와는 거리가 먼, 전혀 다른 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["A stone''s throw from", "A close call with", "A far cry from", "A blind eye to"]', 'The squalid hotel room we were given was ______ the luxurious suite advertised online.', 'en_ad_191', 191, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'At odds with는 ~와 뜻이 맞지 않는, 불화하는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["In line with", "On par with", "In accordance with", "At odds with"]', 'The CEO''s aggressive expansion strategy was constantly ______ the board''s conservative approach.', 'en_ad_192', 192, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'To the detriment of는 ~을 해치면서, ~의 희생으로라는 뜻입니다.', '["To the detriment of", "In the absence of", "For the purpose of", "With the intention of"]', 'He worked eighty hours a week ______, ultimately ruining his marriage and his health.', 'en_ad_193', 193, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'On the premise that은 ~라는 전제 하에라는 뜻입니다.', '["Under the illusion that", "On the premise that", "With the exception that", "To the extent that"]', 'The entire theory is built ______ human beings are inherently rational actors in economics.', 'en_ad_194', 194, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'With regard to는 ~에 관하여(Regarding)라는 뜻입니다.', '["In contrast to", "In response to", "With regard to", "In addition to"]', '______, the committee has decided to postpone the final decision until next month.', 'en_ad_195', 195, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Pertaining to는 ~와 관련된(Related to)이라는 뜻입니다.', '["Resulting from", "Depending on", "Leading to", "Pertaining to"]', 'Please submit all documents ______ your medical history before the examination.', 'en_ad_196', 196, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Conducive to는 ~에 도움이 되는, ~에 좋은 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["conducive to", "vulnerable to", "immune to", "indifferent to"]', 'A noisy, chaotic environment is rarely ______ deep concentration and studying.', 'en_ad_197', 197, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Commensurate with는 ~에 상응하는, 비례하는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["incompatible with", "commensurate with", "oblivious to", "inconsistent with"]', 'Your salary will be highly ______ your level of experience and educational background.', 'en_ad_198', 198, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Tantamount to는 ~와 마찬가지인, ~에 버금가는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["irrelevant to", "subordinate to", "tantamount to", "prior to"]', 'In the military, ignoring a direct order from a superior officer is ______ treason.', 'en_ad_199', 199, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Impervious to는 ~에 영향받지 않는, 휘둘리지 않는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["susceptible to", "prone to", "subject to", "impervious to"]', 'Despite the fierce criticism from the media, the politician remained completely ______ their attacks.', 'en_ad_200', 200, 12);


INSERT INTO quiz_questions (correct_option_index, created_at, explanation, options, question, question_id, sort_order, set_id) VALUES
-- 201~220: Advanced Business Idioms (고급 비즈니스 관용표현)
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Touch base"는 (진행 상황 등을) 연락하여 확인하다라는 뜻의 비즈니스 관용구입니다.', '["touch", "hit", "tag", "cover"]', 'I just wanted to ______ base with you to see how the project is progressing.', 'en_ad_201', 201, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Get the ball rolling"은 (어떤 일을) 시작하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["wheel", "ball", "stone", "gear"]', 'Let''s get the ______ rolling by brainstorming some new marketing strategies.', 'en_ad_202', 202, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Boil the ocean"은 바닷물을 끓인다는 뜻으로, 불가능하거나 지나치게 방대한 일을 하려 하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["freeze", "drain", "boil", "drink"]', 'Focus on a specific target market; trying to appeal to everyone is just trying to ______ the ocean.', 'en_ad_203', 203, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Move the needle"은 상황을 눈에 띄게 바꾸다, 의미 있는 진전을 이루다라는 뜻입니다.', '["dial", "scale", "gauge", "needle"]', 'We need a marketing campaign that will actually move the ______ in terms of sales.', 'en_ad_204', 204, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Low-hanging fruit"는 가장 달성하기 쉬운 목표나 과제를 뜻합니다.', '["fruit", "branch", "leaf", "apple"]', 'Instead of tackling the hardest problems first, let''s go after the low-hanging ______.', 'en_ad_205', 205, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Red tape"은 관료주의, 불필요하게 복잡한 서류 절차를 뜻합니다.', '["blue ribbon", "red tape", "black tie", "white paper"]', 'The startup struggled to secure funding because they had to cut through so much government ______.', 'en_ad_206', 206, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Glass ceiling"은 (여성 등 소수자를 막는) 보이지 않는 장벽, 유리 천장을 뜻합니다.', '["iron curtain", "brick wall", "glass ceiling", "locked door"]', 'She became the first female CEO of the company, finally shattering the ______.', 'en_ad_207', 207, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Bottom line"은 (결산서의 맨 아랫줄인) 순이익, 혹은 가장 핵심적인 사항을 뜻합니다.', '["top tier", "front row", "center stage", "bottom line"]', 'You can give me all the excuses you want, but the ______ is that we lost the contract.', 'en_ad_208', 208, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Cut corners"는 절차를 무시하다, 편법을 쓰다, 원가를 부당하게 절감하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["corners", "edges", "lines", "paths"]', 'If we cut ______ on the manufacturing process, the quality of our product will suffer.', 'en_ad_209', 209, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Call it a day"는 (그날의 일을) 마무리하다, 퇴근하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["night", "day", "shift", "time"]', 'We have been working on this report for 10 hours. Let''s call it a ______.', 'en_ad_210', 210, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Get down to brass tacks"는 변죽을 울리지 않고 핵심(본론)으로 바로 들어가다라는 뜻입니다.', '["silver nails", "iron bolts", "brass tacks", "golden screws"]', 'Enough small talk. Let''s get down to ______ and discuss the budget.', 'en_ad_211', 211, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Bring to the table"은 (논의, 프로젝트 등에) 기여하다, 유용한 것을 제공하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["desk", "board", "floor", "table"]', 'With his 20 years of experience, he brings a lot of valuable expertise to the ______.', 'en_ad_212', 212, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Hit the ground running"은 새로운 일에 착수하자마자 즉시 전력을 다해 활약하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["running", "walking", "flying", "jumping"]', 'We need to hire someone who can hit the ground ______ from day one.', 'en_ad_213', 213, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"On the same page"는 이해/생각이 일치하다, 상황을 같이 공유하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["book", "page", "chapter", "script"]', 'Before we present this to the client, let''s make sure our team is all on the same ______.', 'en_ad_214', 214, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Think outside the box"는 고정관념/틀을 깨고 창의적으로 생각하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["frame", "circle", "box", "square"]', 'To solve this unprecedented problem, we need to think outside the ______.', 'en_ad_215', 215, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Ahead of the curve"는 유행이나 시대에 앞서가는, 선두를 유지하는 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["line", "wave", "pack", "curve"]', 'By investing in AI technology early, our company has stayed ahead of the ______.', 'en_ad_216', 216, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Go the extra mile"은 특별히 더 애를 쓰다, 기대 이상의 노력을 하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["mile", "yard", "step", "distance"]', 'She is a great employee because she is always willing to go the extra ______ for our clients.', 'en_ad_217', 217, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Learn the ropes"는 (새로운 일의) 요령을 터득하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["strings", "ropes", "wires", "threads"]', 'It will take a few weeks for the new intern to learn the ______ of the office.', 'en_ad_218', 218, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Back to the drawing board"는 실패 후 원점으로(처음부터 다시) 돌아가다라는 뜻입니다.', '["starting line", "whiteboard", "drawing board", "blueprint"]', 'Our proposal was completely rejected, so it''s back to the ______.', 'en_ad_219', 219, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Throw under the bus"는 (자신의 이익을 위해) 동료를 희생양으로 삼다, 배신하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["train", "truck", "car", "bus"]', 'When the project failed, the manager tried to throw his team under the ______ to save his own job.', 'en_ad_220', 220, 12),

-- 221~240: Formal, Legal & Latin Expressions (격식, 법률, 라틴어 차용 관용구)
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Status quo"는 (라틴어) 현재의 상황, 현상을 뜻합니다.', '["Status quo", "Quid pro quo", "Prima facie", "De facto"]', 'Conservatives often prefer to maintain the ______, rather than adopting radical changes.', 'en_ad_221', 221, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Quid pro quo"는 (라틴어) 보상으로 주는 것, 대가성 거래라는 뜻입니다.', '["Per se", "Quid pro quo", "Bona fide", "Ad hoc"]', 'The politician was accused of a ______ arrangement, exchanging political favors for campaign donations.', 'en_ad_222', 222, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Bona fide"는 (라틴어) 진실된, 진짜의, 선의의라는 뜻입니다.', '["Vice versa", "Tabula rasa", "Bona fide", "De jure"]', 'The antique dealer confirmed that the painting was a ______ masterpiece by Picasso.', 'en_ad_223', 223, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Carte blanche"는 (프랑스어) 백지위임장, 전권 위임이라는 뜻입니다.', '["Force majeure", "Faux pas", "Laissez-faire", "Carte blanche"]', 'The director was given ______ to cast whomever he wanted for the leading role.', 'en_ad_224', 224, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Ad hoc"은 (라틴어) 임시로, 특별한 목적을 위해서라는 뜻입니다.', '["Ad hoc", "Ex post facto", "In camera", "Pro rata"]', 'An ______ committee was formed specifically to investigate the sudden financial irregularities.', 'en_ad_225', 225, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Prima facie"는 (라틴어) 언뜻 보기에, 첫인상에라는 뜻의 법률 용어입니다.', '["Ipso facto", "Prima facie", "Modus operandi", "Non sequitur"]', 'There is ______ evidence that the CEO was involved in the embezzlement scheme.', 'en_ad_226', 226, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"De facto"는 (라틴어) (법적으로는 아니더라도) 사실상의, 실질적인 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["De jure", "A priori", "De facto", "Pro bono"]', 'Although he holds no official title, he is the ______ leader of the organization.', 'en_ad_227', 227, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Pro bono"는 (라틴어) 공익을 위해, 무료로(보통 법률 서비스)라는 뜻입니다.', '["Per capita", "Post mortem", "Mutatis mutandis", "Pro bono"]', 'The prestigious law firm requires all its attorneys to take on at least one ______ case a year.', 'en_ad_228', 228, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Modus operandi" (M.O.)는 (라틴어) 작업 방식, (특히 범죄자의) 범행 수법이라는 뜻입니다.', '["Modus operandi", "Habeas corpus", "Caveat emptor", "Persona non grata"]', 'The detective recognized the serial killer''s ______, as the knots tied were identical to previous cases.', 'en_ad_229', 229, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Per se"는 (라틴어) 그 자체로, 본질적으로라는 뜻입니다.', '["Vice versa", "Per se", "Ergo", "Alibi"]', 'I don''t hate the movie ______, but I think the ending was poorly written.', 'en_ad_230', 230, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Vice versa"는 (라틴어) 거꾸로도 마찬가지다, 역도 성립한다라는 뜻입니다.', '["Et cetera", "Ad infinitum", "Vice versa", "Erratum"]', 'He doesn''t trust me, and ______, I do not trust him either.', 'en_ad_231', 231, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Ipso facto"는 (라틴어) 그 사실 자체로, 결과적으로 당연히라는 뜻입니다.', '["In vitro", "In situ", "In absentia", "Ipso facto"]', 'If you sign this contract, you are, ______, agreeing to the confidentiality clause.', 'en_ad_232', 232, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Sine qua non"은 (라틴어) 필수 불가결한 요소, 절대적 조건이라는 뜻입니다.', '["Sine qua non", "Mea culpa", "Magnum opus", "Lingua franca"]', 'Trust is the ______ of any successful marriage.', 'en_ad_233', 233, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Caveat emptor"는 (라틴어) 매수인 위험 부담 원칙(구매자가 물건의 하자를 확인해야 함)을 뜻합니다.', '["Carpe diem", "Caveat emptor", "Coup de grace", "Cui bono"]', 'When buying a used car from a private seller, the rule of ______ strongly applies.', 'en_ad_234', 234, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Ultra vires"는 (라틴어) 권한을 넘은, 월권 행위의라는 뜻의 법률/경영 용어입니다.', '["In loco parentis", "Sub poena", "Ultra vires", "Amicus curiae"]', 'The board of directors declared the CEO''s unauthorized purchase of the property to be ______.', 'en_ad_235', 235, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Verbatim"은 말 그대로, 글자 하나 안 틀리고 똑같이(word for word)라는 뜻입니다.', '["Arbitrary", "Superficial", "Ambiguous", "Verbatim"]', 'The journalist transcribed the president''s speech ______, ensuring no quotes were taken out of context.', 'en_ad_236', 236, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"A priori"는 (라틴어) 선험적인, 연역적인(경험하기 전에 논리적으로 추론하는) 이라는 뜻입니다.', '["A priori", "A posteriori", "Ad nauseam", "Bona fide"]', 'Mathematical truths are often considered ______ knowledge, independent of empirical experience.', 'en_ad_237', 237, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Non sequitur"는 (라틴어) 불합리한 추론, 전제와 무관한 결론이라는 뜻입니다.', '["Deus ex machina", "Non sequitur", "Alter ego", "Vox populi"]', 'His response to the serious question was a bizarre ______ about his favorite flavor of ice cream.', 'en_ad_238', 238, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Tabula rasa"는 (라틴어) 백지 상태, 아무것도 없는 상태라는 뜻입니다.', '["Terra incognita", "Magna carta", "Tabula rasa", "Alma mater"]', 'John Locke argued that the human mind at birth is a ______, shaped entirely by experience.', 'en_ad_239', 239, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Esprit de corps"는 (프랑스어) 단체 정신, 동지애, 결속력이라는 뜻입니다.', '["Fait accompli", "Coup d''etat", "Joie de vivre", "Esprit de corps"]', 'The intense military training fostered a strong sense of ______ among the platoon members.', 'en_ad_240', 240, 12),

-- 241~260: Advanced Daily Idioms 1 (고급 일상/관계 관용표현)
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Give the cold shoulder"는 ~를 냉대하다, 쌀쌀맞게 대하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["shoulder", "eye", "hand", "back"]', 'After our argument, she gave me the cold ______ at the party.', 'en_ad_241', 241, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Give the benefit of the doubt"는 (확실치 않을 때) 좋은 쪽으로 해석하다, 속는 셈 치고 믿어주다라는 뜻입니다.', '["proof", "doubt", "trust", "truth"]', 'I''m not sure if he is lying, but I will give him the benefit of the ______ for now.', 'en_ad_242', 242, 12),
(2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Play devil''s advocate"는 (토론을 위해) 일부러 반대 입장을 취하다, 딴지를 걸다라는 뜻입니다.', '["angel''s", "god''s", "devil''s", "demon''s"]', 'I agree with your plan, but let me play ______ advocate to test its flaws.', 'en_ad_243', 243, 12),
(3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Take with a grain of salt"는 (정보 등을) 곧이곧대로 믿지 않고 걸러 듣다, 가감해서 듣다라는 뜻입니다.', '["sugar", "pepper", "sand", "salt"]', 'He exaggerates a lot, so you should take everything he says with a grain of ______.', 'en_ad_244', 244, 12),
(0, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Bury the hatchet"은 무기를 묻다, 즉 화해하다, 싸움을 멈추다라는 뜻입니다.', '["hatchet", "sword", "gun", "knife"]', 'After years of feuding, the two brothers finally decided to bury the ______ and make peace.', 'en_ad_245', 245, 12),
(1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '"Sit on the fence"는 (결정을 내리지 않고) 중립을 지키다, 형세를 관망하다라는 뜻입니다.', '["wall", "fence", "chair", "bridge"]', 'You can''t sit on the ______ forever; eventually, you have to choose a side.', 'en_ad_246', 246, 12),
